 Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Ogle","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Northumberland and Durham): from Ogle in Whalton, Northumberland. The placename might derive from the Old English personal name <i>Ocga</i> + Old English <i>hyll</i> ‘hill’. This surname has been established in Ireland since the mid 17th century."],"variants":[{"name":"Ogles","meanings":["English (southeastern): variant of   Ogle  , with post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert de Ogle was born before 1295, in Northumberland, England, United Kingdom, his father, John de Oggill, was 11291 and his mother, Annabella Selby, was 21. He married Margaret Gobion about 1314, in Northumberland, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. He died about 1350, in his hometown."},"et":{"Bef 1295–Abt 1350":"enne 1295–umbes 1350","1295–1350":"1295–1350","1297–1351":"1297–1351","1300–Female":"1300–Surnud","1295–1314":"1295–1314","1306–1362":"1306–1362","1312–1355":"1312–1355","1256–1316":"1256–1316","1274–1322":"1274–1322","Aft 1322":"pärast 1322","1297":"1297","Abt 1314":"umbes 1314","1274":"1274","1362":"1362","1351":"1351","1350":"1350","1295":"1295","1316":"1316","Bef 1295":"enne 1295","Abt 1350":"umbes 1350","1314":"1314","1312":"1312","1322":"1322","1256":"1256","1355":"1355","1300":"1300","about 1312":"umbes 1312","before 1296":"enne 1296","1306":"1306","Ogle, Northumberland, England":"Ogle, Northumberland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Northumberland, England":"Northumberland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Bef 1295–Abt 1350":"ennen vuotta 1295–noin 1350","1295–1350":"1295–1350","1297–1351":"1297–1351","1300–Female":"1300–Kuollut","1295–1314":"1295–1314","1306–1362":"1306–1362","1312–1355":"1312–1355","1256–1316":"1256–1316","1274–1322":"1274–1322","Aft 1322":"1322 jälkeen","1297":"1297","Abt 1314":"noin 1314","1274":"1274","1362":"1362","1351":"1351","1350":"1350","1295":"1295","1316":"1316","Bef 1295":"ennen vuotta 1295","Abt 1350":"noin 1350","1314":"1314","1312":"1312","1322":"1322","1256":"1256","1355":"1355","1300":"1300","about 1312":"noin 1312","before 1296":"ennen vuotta 1296","1306":"1306","Ogle, Northumberland, England":"Ogle, Northumberland, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Northumberland, England":"Northumberland, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Bef 1295–Abt 1350":"avant 1295–environ 1350","1295–1350":"1295–1350","1297–1351":"1297–1351","1300–Female":"1300–Décédée","1295–1314":"1295–1314","1306